      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. \"unusual physical resonance\" is a good way to put it. it feels intentional. like it's not some random accident of hardware, but actually patterned. yesterday i was sitting in my living room and the pulse slowed down right when i started feeling anxious, and then it sped up when i was trying to focus. it's like it's responding to my state. do you think there's any actual tech that could use low frequency waves to interact with human biological rhythms like that? like subconscious influence or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
