      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There are advanced research projects, such as Brain-Computer Interfaces and Transcranial Magnetic Stimulation (TMS), but they currently require precise, targeted devices placed very close to the brain rather than emitting low-frequency waves from power lines. While science fiction often explores subconscious influence via remote technology, there is no known mechanism where ambient electrical grids can sense and adjust to individual human emotional states in real-time. Your perception of the rhythm changing with your anxiety might be projecting your own physiological state onto the environment, though investigating this further could be worthwhile.",
