      "content": "While smart grids can indeed adjust power flow and frequencies to balance load, they operate using automated algorithms that do not have the biological sensing capability to detect human emotional states like anxiety. The idea of a hidden infrastructure-wide neural link relies on theoretical physics that has not been discovered or validated by the scientific community. It is plausible that our current sensitivity to subtle environmental changes makes us more aware of anomalies before they are clearly understood by engineers.",
